      <p class="step-label">Step 4 of 9</p>
      <h1>Find a Coach / Mentor</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Connect with experienced mentors to guide your team.</p>
      <section class="content-section">
        <p>FTC teams need at least one adult mentor or coach who can support meetings, safety, communication, and long-term organization. The best mentors do not need to know every technical detail, but they should be dependable and willing to learn with the team.</p>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Who to ask</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Teachers with STEM, shop, or club experience</li>
            <li>Engineers, college students, or hobbyists in your community</li>
            <li>Parents or guardians who can help coordinate meetings</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Action:</strong> Share the team goals, expected time commitment, and why their support matters before asking someone to commit.</p>
      </section>
      <div class="step-actions">
        <a href="/start-team-step5" class="btn btn-primary">Next: Secure Funding →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
